## 💳 STRIPE INTEGRATION (CORRECT APPROACH)

### **Architecture**:
1. Next.js pages (rensto.com) contain buttons/components
2. Buttons call `/api/stripe/checkout` (relative path) or `https://rensto.com/api/stripe/checkout`
3. API route creates Stripe session, returns checkout URL
4. User redirects to Stripe, completes payment
5. Stripe webhook sends event to `https://rensto.com/api/stripe/webhook` (or `api.rensto.com/api/stripe/webhook`)
6. Webhook handler triggers n8n workflows

### **Workflow**:
```
Next.js Button → rensto.com/api/stripe/checkout → Stripe Checkout
                                                           ↓
Stripe Webhook → rensto.com/api/stripe/webhook → n8n STRIPE-* workflows
```

**Note**: Both `rensto.com/api/*` and `api.rensto.com/api/*` work (same source code)

### **Active Stripe n8n Workflows**:
- `STRIPE-MARKETPLACE-001`: Template purchases
- `STRIPE-INSTALL-001`: Installation services
- `STRIPE-READY-001`: Ready Solutions packages
- `STRIPE-SUBSCRIPTION-001`: Monthly subscriptions
- `STRIPE-CUSTOM-001`: Custom solutions projects
- `DEV-FIN-006`: Revenue sync (legacy; migrating to Postgres)

