## 📊 DATA STORAGE HIERARCHY

### **Priority Order** (ALWAYS follow this – see CLAUDE.md for full matrix):
1. **PRIMARY (app/customer data)**: PostgreSQL (service instances, customers, payments) – used by rensto-site
2. **CACHE/QUEUE**: Redis (sessions, rate limits, job queues)
3. **OPERATIONAL**: Antigravity (primary automation); n8n (backup only)
4. **LEGACY/REFERENCE**: Firestore (retired, fallback reads only — migration complete Feb 2026), Airtable.com (retired); **Aitable.ai** (in use for dashboards); Notion (docs)

### **Never Store In**:
- ❌ MongoDB (unless customer project >50K records)
- ❌ Supabase (unless custom customer app with real-time requirements)

